# Rocket.new — Memory Bank Protocol

> Cursor's memory resets completely between sessions.
> The memory-bank/ directory is the external brain that survives resets.
> READ IT at the start of every session. UPDATE IT after every significant fix or decision.

---

## MANDATORY: START OF EVERY SESSION

Before touching any code in this project, read these files in order:

```
1. memory-bank/project-context.md    — what this project is, its current state
2. memory-bank/active-issues.md      — what's currently broken or in progress
3. memory-bank/patterns-discovered.md — Rocket-specific quirks found in THIS codebase
4. memory-bank/fixes-applied.md      — what was already tried and what worked/failed
```

If these files don't exist yet → create them using the templates below.

**This is not optional.** Reading memory-bank/ before acting is what separates a fresh useful session from a session that undoes yesterday's work.

---

## MANDATORY: END OF EVERY SIGNIFICANT SESSION

After fixing a bug, implementing a feature, or making any architectural decision:

```
1. Update memory-bank/fixes-applied.md with what you did and why
2. Update memory-bank/active-issues.md (remove resolved, add new)
3. Update memory-bank/patterns-discovered.md if you found a new codebase quirk
4. Update memory-bank/project-context.md if the project state changed significantly
```

Trigger phrase: when the developer says "update memory" or "save session" → execute all 4 updates above.

